description: From a 1920s trade name for automotive lacquer.

examples: A green four-wheel drive, its duco iridescent in the winter sunlight like the carapace of some mythical beetle come to rest there, was parked by the side of a ripple-iron tank set back from the riverbank.

verbs.description: duco (third-person singular simple present ducos, present participle ducoing, simple past and past participle ducoed)

entries.meaning: (Australia, automotive, colloquial, transitive) To paint with automotive paint.
